column13:
I added some extra formatting for human readability and a quick average to see how many steps are taken on average. The formatting looks better in eclipse - I think the kerning of this font makes it look weird in the text boxes.

What I fixed since last night: the whole problem was an off by one error that made run() attempt to access out of range elements /facepalm. I fixed it by changing moveNum to go from 0-7 instead of 1-8 and checking every place that used moveNum.
My main method now runs run() several times, then reports the amount of steps made in each attempt and spits out an average.

The formatting now uses printf() instead of the stopgap "\t"s to look nicer and more condensed.
